\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. F. aegaea} Wagenitz, {\i Willdenowia}{\b  6}: 126 (1970). Plant greyish-white. Stem up to 6 cm. Capitula ovoid, subterete, in clusters of 5-15; clusters 7-10 × 8-12 mm, not or scarcely overtopped by subtending leaves. Involucral bracts ovate-lanceolate, more or less rigid, completely tomentose in the upper part, curved obliquely inwards in fruit. Female florets 12-15, all but 0-5 marginal, the hermaphrodite 5-8. Achenes 0·7-0·9 × 0·4 mm, brown. Pappus 1·5 mm.{\i  Ionioi Nisoi; S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
