\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. F. cretensis} Gand., {\i Fl. Cret.} 58 (1916). Stem up to 6(-12) cm. Leaves 10-15 × 1-3·5 mm, oblanceolate to spathulate, glabrescent above, the lower petiolate. Capitula subterete, in terminal clusters of 5-7; clusters 4-6 mm wide, more or less overtopped by several subtending leaves. Involucral bracts ovate-lanceolate, soft, purplish to brownish, suberect or slightly divergent in fruit. Inner female florets 8-12; hermaphrodite 3-6(-8). Achenes c. 0·7 mm, brown. Pappus 1-1·2 mm.{\i  S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
